<h2>4. Functional Requirements</h2>

<h3>4.1 Authentication & Access</h3>
<ul>
    <li>FR-1.1: System shall require username/password login for admin access</li>
    <li>FR-1.2: Passwords shall be encrypted before storage</li>
    <li>FR-1.3: Sessions shall expire after inactivity</li>
    <li>FR-1.4: OTP verification for password reset</li>
</ul>

<h3>4.2 Multi-Language Support</h3>
<p><strong>Supported Languages:</strong> Arabic, Chinese, Dutch, English, French, German, Greek, Hindi, Italian, Portuguese, Russian, Sinhala, Spanish</p>

<h2>5. Security Requirements</h2>
<table>
    <tr><th>Category</th><th>Requirement</th></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Encryption</strong></td><td>All passwords encrypted using BCrypt algorithm</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Authorization</strong></td><td>Role-based access control (RBAC)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Audit</strong></td><td>All admin actions logged with timestamp and user</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Backup</strong></td><td>Secure database backups daily</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>6. Glossary of Terms</h2>
<table>
    <tr><th>Term</th><th>Definition</th></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Admin Panel</strong></td><td>The secure password-protected area where staff members manage website content.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>API</strong></td><td>The "bridge" that allows the public website to communicate with the database.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Audit Log</strong></td><td>A permanent security record that tracks who performed what action and when.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>CMS</strong></td><td>Software that allows users to create and manage digital content without writing code.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Frontend</strong></td><td>The visible part of the website that visitors interact with.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>GridFS</strong></td><td>A specialized storage system used for handling large files like user CVs.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>JWT</strong></td><td>A digital "key card" for secure login sessions.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Maker-Checker</strong></td><td>A security workflow where one person creates changes and another must approve them.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>OTP</strong></td><td>One-Time Password used for identity verification.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Super Admin</strong></td><td>The highest-level user role with full control over the system.</td></tr>
</table>

